        "Name": "Broadside",
        "Details": "Developed by Iroquois Machinery Limited as their first entry into true BattleMech production, the Broadside has been met with heavy skepticism by Davion MechWarriors. However, after an impressive showing from a cadet in the 1st Conroe Training Battalion against a Kuritan Atlas, the Broadside is coming to be more broadly accepted. The design is built around a 300-rated fusion engine with Endo-Steel bones for extra weight saving. True to its Davion roots, the Broadside uses a mixture of autocannons for primary firepower (a LB-10X, UAC/10, and RAC/2 specifically). For backup, the Broadside carries a brace of lasers and a flamer. The dense armor provides more than enough protection while CASE II protects the substantial ammunition bins.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
